race.description: Lovatsville Gold Trip @ Stud For $8,800 Mdn Plt
race.comment: Lots of these close to getting off the mark. THINKING SENSATION (7) has placed all three this time in including two back on soft ground at Echuca. Should be prominent off the low draw and will give a sight again. AUSTRAL MISS (8) was fifth on debut then found the line strongly in wet ground for a close-up fourth. Back to her home track and should be winding up late. KINGSFORD (4) is the one to watch for a strong push. Has placed 3/5 so far and all three on rain-affected ground. Returns from a break and will want much further in time but presents on the back of two jump-outs at home and might be too smart fresh. MALAWI MAN (5) is another close to a win, finishing fourth two back then runner-up latest. Off a low draw and can give a sight. ELEANOR DUMONT (13) is a former Kiwi who was safely held at first start for a new yard and given another break. Looks to have good upside and is worth keeping safe.
